{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Last year at TED I gave an introduction to the LHC."},{"time":4000,"text":"And I promised to come back and give you an update"},{"time":6000,"text":"on how that machine worked."},{"time":8000,"text":"So this is it. And for those of you that weren't there,"},{"time":10000,"text":"the LHC is the largest scientific experiment ever attempted --"},{"time":13000,"text":"27 kilometers in circumference."},{"time":15000,"text":"Its job is to recreate the conditions"},{"time":17000,"text":"that were present less than a billionth of a second after the universe began,"},{"time":20000,"text":"up to 600 million times a second."},{"time":23000,"text":"It's nothing if not ambitious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"This is the machine below Geneva."},{"time":27000,"text":"We take the pictures of those mini-Big Bangs inside detectors."},{"time":30000,"text":"This is the one I work on. It's called the ATLAS detector --"},{"time":33000,"text":"44 meters wide, 22 meters in diameter."},{"time":36000,"text":"Spectacular picture here of ATLAS under construction"},{"time":39000,"text":"so you can see the scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"On the 10th of September last year we turned the machine on for the first time."},{"time":44000,"text":"And this picture was taken by ATLAS."},{"time":47000,"text":"It caused immense celebration in the control room."},{"time":50000,"text":"It's a picture of the first beam particle"},{"time":52000,"text":"going all the way around the LHC,"},{"time":54000,"text":"colliding with a piece of the LHC deliberately,"},{"time":57000,"text":"and showering particles into the detector."},{"time":59000,"text":"In other words, when we saw that picture on September 10th"},{"time":61000,"text":"we knew the machine worked,"},{"time":63000,"text":"which is a great triumph."},{"time":65000,"text":"I don't know whether this got the biggest cheer,"},{"time":67000,"text":"or this, when someone went onto Google"},{"time":69000,"text":"and saw the front page was like that."},{"time":71000,"text":"It means we made cultural impact"},{"time":73000,"text":"as well as scientific impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"About a week later we had a problem with the machine,"},{"time":78000,"text":"related actually to these bits of wire here -- these gold wires."},{"time":82000,"text":"Those wires carry 13 thousand amps"},{"time":85000,"text":"when the machine is working in full power."},{"time":87000,"text":"Now the engineers amongst you will look at them and say,"},{"time":89000,"text":"\"No they don't. They're small wires.\""},{"time":91000,"text":"They can do that because"},{"time":93000,"text":"when they are very cold they are what's called superconducting wire."},{"time":95000,"text":"So at minus 271 degrees,"},{"time":98000,"text":"colder than the space between the stars,"},{"time":100000,"text":"those wires can take that current."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"In one of the joints between over 9,000 magnets in LHC,"},{"time":106000,"text":"there was a manufacturing defect."},{"time":108000,"text":"So the wire heated up slightly,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and its 13,000 amps suddenly encountered electrical resistance."},{"time":114000,"text":"This was the result."},{"time":116000,"text":"Now that's more impressive"},{"time":119000,"text":"when you consider those magnets weigh over 20 tons,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and they moved about a foot."},{"time":123000,"text":"So we damaged about 50 of the magnets."},{"time":126000,"text":"We had to take them out, which we did."},{"time":129000,"text":"We reconditioned them all, fixed them."},{"time":131000,"text":"They're all on their way back underground now."},{"time":133000,"text":"By the end of March the LHC will be intact again."},{"time":135000,"text":"We will switch it on,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and we expect to take data in June or July,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and continue with our quest to find out"},{"time":143000,"text":"what the building blocks of the universe are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Now of course, in a way"},{"time":148000,"text":"those accidents reignite the debate"},{"time":150000,"text":"about the value of science and engineering at the edge. It's easy to refute."},{"time":156000,"text":"I think that the fact that it's so difficult,"},{"time":158000,"text":"the fact that we're overreaching, is the value of things like the LHC."},{"time":162000,"text":"I will leave the final word to an English scientist, Humphrey Davy,"},{"time":166000,"text":"who, I suspect,"},{"time":168000,"text":"when defending his protege's useless experiments --"},{"time":171000,"text":"his protege was Michael Faraday --"},{"time":173000,"text":"said this, \"Nothing is so dangerous"},{"time":176000,"text":"to the progress of the human mind"},{"time":178000,"text":"than to assume that our views of science are ultimate,"},{"time":182000,"text":"that there are no mysteries in nature,"},{"time":184000,"text":"that our triumphs are complete, and that"},{"time":186000,"text":"there are no new worlds to conquer.\""},{"time":188000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":190000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}